Detailed Description

cvmx_pko_reg_read_idx

Notes: Provides the read index during a CSR read operation to any of the CSRs that are physically stored as memories. The names of these CSRs begin with the prefix "PKO_MEM_". IDX[7:0] is the read index. INC[7:0] is an increment that is added to IDX[7:0] after any CSR read. The intended use is to initially write this CSR such that IDX=0 and INC=1. Then, the entire contents of a CSR memory can be read with consecutive CSR read commands.
